    {
      "paragraph_name": "UNLOAD",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This step executes the IMS program DFSRRC00 to unload the DBD DBPAUTP0. It sets the region size to 4M and passes parameters (ULU, DFSURGU0, DBPAUTP0) to the program. The STEPLIB DD statements define the libraries containing the necessary IMS modules. The DFSRESLB DD statement defines the IMS RESLIB. The IMS DD statements define the PSBLIB and DBDLIB. The DFSURGU1 DD statement defines the output dataset where the unloaded DBD will be stored, specifying its disposition, unit, space allocation, and DCB attributes. The DDPAUTP0 and DDPAUTX0 DD statements define the PAUTHDB and PAUTHDBX datasets. The DFSVSAMP DD statement defines the VSAMP dataset. The DFSCTL DD statement defines control parameters, in this case, SBPARM ACTIV=COND. The SYSUDUMP DD statement defines the system dump dataset. The RECON* DD statements define the RECON datasets. The DFSWRK01 and DFSSRT01 DD statements define dummy datasets. This step performs the core function of unloading the DBD. Any errors during the unload process will be handled by IMS and potentially result in a system dump. It does not call any other programs or paragraphs directly, but relies on DFSRRC00 to perform the unload operation.",
      "called_by": [],
      "calls": [],
